@startuml "Job Manager Class Diagram"
title "Background Process Management: JobManager Architecture"

' ==================== JOB MANAGER TYPES ====================

package "Job Management" {
  ' JobStatus enum
  enum JobStatus {
    Running
    Done(i32)
    Terminated
  }

  note right of JobStatus
    **Job Lifecycle**
    - Running: Process is active
    - Done(exit_code): Process completed with exit code
    - Terminated: Process was terminated by signal

    **Display Implementation**
    Formats as human-readable strings:
    - "Running"
    - "Done (exit: 0)"
    - "Terminated"
  end note

  ' JobInfo - public job information (cloneable, displayable)
  class JobInfo {
    + id: usize
    + pid: u32
    + command: String
    + status: JobStatus
    + start_time: Instant
    --
    + All fields public
    + Cloneable for safe display
  }

  note right of JobInfo
    **Job Information (Public)**
    Safe structure for job metadata:
    - id: 1-based job ID (bash-style)
    - pid: Process ID from spawned child
    - command: Original command string (including "&")
    - status: Current job status
    - start_time: When job was started

    **Cloneable Design**
    Returns cloned JobInfo from JobManager,
    allowing safe iteration and display
    without lock contention.
  end note

  ' JobEntry - internal, holds Child process
  class JobEntry {
    - info: JobInfo
    - child: Child
    --
    - Internal use only
    - Holds mutable Child for status checking
  }

  note right of JobEntry
    **Internal Job Entry**
    Pairs JobInfo with Tokio Child process:
    - Enables try_wait() for status checking
    - Not exposed publicly (JobInfo only)

    **Private Fields**
    Child is private to JobManager,
    preventing external process manipulation.
  end note

  ' JobManager - main job tracking structure
  class JobManager {
    - jobs: HashMap<usize, JobEntry>
    - next_id: usize
    --
    + new(): Self
    + add_job(command: String, pid: u32, child: Child) -> usize
    + list_jobs(): Vec<JobInfo>
    + job_count(): usize
    + check_completed() -> Vec<JobInfo>
    + remove_job(id: usize) -> Option<JobInfo>
    + has_running_jobs(): bool
  }

  note top of JobManager
    **Background Job Manager**
    Single source of truth for job tracking:

    **Responsibilities**
    - Track spawned background processes
    - Monitor completion status
    - Maintain job table with 1-based IDs

    **Key Methods**
    - add_job(): Assign ID, store job, return job_id
    - check_completed(): Poll all jobs, update status, return completed
    - list_jobs(): Return cloned JobInfo for display (no lock contention)
    - remove_job(): Remove finished job from table

    **Thread Safety**
    - Accessed only via SharedJobManager (Arc<RwLock<>>)
    - RwLock allows many concurrent readers
    - Write lock only during add/check_completed
  end note

  ' SharedJobManager type alias
  note as SharedNote
    **Shared Job Manager**
    type SharedJobManager = Arc<RwLock<JobManager>>

    **Arc**: Shared ownership across threads
    **RwLock**: Read-write synchronization

    **Usage Pattern**
    {
      let mut mgr = job_manager.write()?;
      let job_id = mgr.add_job(...);
    }

    {
      let mgr = job_manager.read()?;
      let jobs = mgr.list_jobs();
    }
  end note

  ' Helper function
  class JobManagerFactory {
    + create_shared_job_manager(): SharedJobManager
  }

  note right of JobManagerFactory
    **Factory Function**
    Convenience for creating shared:
    Arc::new(RwLock::new(JobManager::new()))
  end note

  JobManager --> JobEntry : owns (internal)
  JobManager --> JobInfo : returns cloned
  JobEntry --> JobInfo : wraps
  JobEntry --> "tokio::process::Child" : holds
  JobManagerFactory --> JobManager : creates shared
}

' ==================== RELATIONSHIPS ====================

package "Integration Points" {
  class CommandExecutor {
    + is_background_command(input: &str) -> bool
    + execute_background(cmd: &str, job_mgr: &SharedJobManager) -> Result<(usize, u32)>
  }

  note right of CommandExecutor
    **Background Command Detection & Execution**
    - is_background_command(): Detects trailing "&"
    - execute_background(): Spawns job, gets PID, adds to manager
  end note

  class CommandOrchestrator {
    + handle_command(..., job_manager: &SharedJobManager) -> Result<()>
    + handle_jobs_command(..., job_manager: &SharedJobManager) -> Result<()>
    + execute_background_and_display(...) -> Result<()>
  }

  note right of CommandOrchestrator
    **Job Orchestration**
    - Routing: Detects background commands
    - Execution: Calls CommandExecutor::execute_background
    - Listing: Shows jobs with handle_jobs_command
  end note

  class InfrawareTerminal {
    - job_manager: SharedJobManager
    - last_job_check: Instant
    --
    + check_completed_jobs()
    - Event loop integration (periodic checking)
  }

  note right of InfrawareTerminal
    **Main App Integration (Periodic Job Checking)**
    - Holds SharedJobManager field
    - Holds last_job_check: Instant for tracking

    **Event Loop Integration**
    In main event loop:
    - After handling events: check if elapsed >= JOB_CHECK_INTERVAL
    - Also check during timeout select arm (every 100ms timeout)
    - Call check_completed_jobs() periodically
    - Reset last_job_check = Instant::now()

    **check_completed_jobs() Method**
    - Acquire read lock: check has_running_jobs()
    - If no jobs, return early (fast path)
    - Acquire write lock: call check_completed()
    - Handle poisoned locks with fail-fast (log + return)
    - Display completion notifications to user
  end note

  CommandExecutor --> JobManager : adds jobs via
  CommandOrchestrator --> CommandExecutor : calls for execution
  CommandOrchestrator --> JobManager : queries list, handles "jobs" builtin
  InfrawareTerminal --> JobManager : monitors via check_completed()
}

' ==================== FLOW NOTES ====================

package "Typical Workflow" {
  note as WorkflowNote
    **Background Command Execution Flow**

    1. **Input Classification**
       User enters: "sleep 10 &"
       InputClassifier → InputType::Command (original_input = "sleep 10 &")

    2. **Routing**
       CommandOrchestrator detects background via is_background_command()
       Calls execute_background_and_display()

    3. **Job Spawning**
       CommandExecutor::execute_background():
       - Removes trailing "&"
       - Spawns tokio process (bash -c "sleep 10")
       - Gets PID from child.id()
       - Calls job_manager.write().add_job(...)
       - Returns (job_id, pid)

    4. **Display Feedback**
       Displays: "[1] sleep 10 & (PID: 12345)"

    5. **Job Monitoring** (Continuous in Event Loop)
       InfrawareTerminal::check_completed_jobs():
       - Calls job_manager.write().check_completed()
       - Receives list of just-completed jobs
       - Displays completion status to user

    6. **Manual Listing**
       User enters: "jobs"
       handle_jobs_command():
       - Calls job_manager.read().list_jobs()
       - Displays all active and completed jobs

    7. **Cleanup**
       Completed jobs are automatically removed
       from manager after status is polled
  end note
}

' ==================== DESIGN PATTERNS ====================

package "Design Patterns" {
  note as PatternsNote
    **RAII Pattern**
    Child process is dropped when JobEntry is removed,
    ensuring process resources are cleaned up.

    **Lazy Singleton**
    JobManager created once, shared via Arc<RwLock<>>.

    **Fail-Fast Lock Poisoning (not Recovery)**
    If RwLock poisoned:
    - Log error: "JobManager lock poisoned"
    - Return early: bail/return without trying to recover
    - Don't use .into_inner() - avoid corrupted state
    - Graceful degradation: skip check, UI stays responsive
    - Prevents cascade failures from panics in locked code

    **Non-Blocking Status Check**
    try_wait() is non-blocking - won't freeze UI.
    Perfect for periodic polling in event loop.

    **Periodic Checking with 250ms Interval**
    JOB_CHECK_INTERVAL = Duration::from_millis(250)
    - Checked via last_job_check: Instant tracking
    - Balances responsiveness vs lock contention
    - Avoids acquisition on every keystroke

    **Clone-Safe Public API**
    JobInfo is Cloneable, enabling safe reads
    without locking manager during iteration.

    **Fast Path Optimization**
    - Read lock first: check has_running_jobs()
    - Only write lock if jobs exist
    - Reduces unnecessary lock contention
  end note
}

@enduml
